= Taxes

In this chapter we shall discuss those taxes — the levies, the offerings
(_nazrana_), and the homage-payments (_salam_) — which, according to the
statement of the reformists, the _Amil_ gentlemen collect in the name of
the chief Mullaji. In Section "C" of the questionnaire we had included
questions on this matter, and all the respondents stated in their answers
that taxes of the following kinds are collected:

